1. To go to home folder from anywhere. type "CD ~/" and enter.
2. Replace a string in Vi editor --> %s/str1/str2
3. Repeat the line (Y in esc mode and p)
4. Delete the line D
5. Exiting

:x	-> Exit, saving changes
:q	-> Exit as long as there have been no changes
ZZ	-> Exit and save changes if any have been made
:q!	-> Exit and ignore any changes

cheatsheat.
http://www.lagmonster.org/docs/vi.html

6. file-name|wc -l -> gives number of lines.
